history.content:
Interested in data science, business analytics, free food, or free raffle prizes?

Alpha Kappa Psi is hosting a data industry event called “Demystifying Data” this evening where weʼll have speakers from tech companies including Apple and Airbnb come speak about how they use data in the industry and how theyʼve translated what they learned in their classes to their job. Youʼll also have the chance to network with them and to drop off your resume. Weʼll also have free Sliver and Gong Cha and be raffling off some prizes including Airpods.

The event will be tonight (Thursday) from 6:30 PM - 9:30 PM at Andersen Auditorium at the Haas School of Business. See the event flyer below or click “Going” on our Facebook event to see more. Hope to see you there!

Facebook event: www.facebook.com/events/1789969561147082/

Flyer: Demystifying_Data_Flyer.pdf
